steps.instruction:
- Preheat a large stockpot on medium-high heat for 2 to 3 minutes
- Place oil, onions and peppers in pan, cook for 2 minutes
- Remove sausage casing by cutting almost in half lengthwise (butterfly), turn sausage over and peel casings away
- Add sausage, both seasonings, red pepper and salt
- Brown for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring to crumble meat
- Stir in tomatoes, pumpkin, stock and gnocchi, then cover
- Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring occasionally

Notes:  
- You can also use mild pork sausage instead of chicken  
- These spice blends are readily available during the fall months. Other times of the year you can substitute with graham masala  
- For a richer taste, reduce heat to low just after you brown the meat and do not add the pasta. Cover and simmer for 1 hour, add gnocchi during the last 5 minutes  
- Great with a salad and garlic bread with and pumpkin pie for dessert
